recap.summary: Aaron Rodgers doesn't have to lay waste to a defense to enjoy Packers football.  ''Yeah, it was fun to watch,'' Rodgers said after Green Bay opened the NFL's 100th season with a 10-3 victory over Chicago.  A lack of action in the preseason clearly damaged both offenses, and Rodgers at times looked uncomfortable in the attack designed by new coach Matt LaFleur.
recap.author: BARRY WILNER (AP Pro Football Writer)
recap.short_title: Packers' D, Aaron Rodgers beat Bears 10-3 in opener
